About picto
-----------

Picto is a plugin for photo management and sharing between users of your social network.


Plugin requirements
-------------------

In case you haven't installed any of them previously:

- acts_as_commentable: 

		-This is a requirement for tog, so you should have already installed it!.

- acts_as_taggable_on_steroids: http://svn.viney.net.nz/things/rails/plugins/acts_as_taggable_on_steroids/README

		For those of you impatient:
		
			1.- install plugin:        
						script/plugin install http://svn.viney.net.nz/things/rails/plugins/acts_as_taggable_on_steroids
						
			2.- generate migration:    
						script/generate acts_as_taggable_migration

- rateableplugin: http://rateableplugin.rubyforge.org/

		For the impatients:

       1.- install plugin:              
						script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/rateableplugin/trunk
						
       2.- generate migration:   
						script/generate migration add_ratings 

					class AddRatings < ActiveRecord::Migration
						def self.up
			        create_table :ratings do |t|
			                t.column :rating, :integer    # You can add a default value here if you wish
			                t.column :rateable_id :integer, :null => false
			                t.column :rateable_type, :string, :null => false
			        end
			        add_index :ratings, [:rateable_id, :rating]    # Not required, but should help more than it hurts
						end

						def self.down
					    drop_table :ratings
						end
				  end
				
- acts_as_list: http://github.com/rails/acts_as_list/tree/master/README

			1.- install plugin:
					 script/plugin install git://github.com/rails/acts_as_list.git 


Installation
------------

1.- Download source:
			 
			(TODO: update with public URL if necessary!)
			script/plugin install git@github.com:tog/tog_picto.git
				
2.- Generate installation migration:

      script/generate migration install_picto

	  with the following content:
	
			class InstallPicto < ActiveRecord::Migration
			  def self.up
			    migrate_plugin "tog_picto", 6
			  end

			  def self.down
			    migrate_plugin "tog_picto", 0
			  end
			end
			
3.- Add picto's routes to your application's config/routes.rb
			
			map.routes_from_plugin 'tog_picto'

			
Post installation
-----------------

1.- Run your new migrations:

			rake db:migrate